{"title_page": "Ogden Hoffman Jr.", "text_new": "{{Short description|American judge}}\n{{Infobox judge\n| name          = Ogden Hoffman Jr.\n| image         = Ogden Hoffman, Jr. (Federal judge of California).jpg\n| caption       = Judge Ogden Hoffman Jr. ''San Francisco Call'', December 19, 1893.\n| office        = Judge of the [[United States District Court for the Northern District of California]]\n| term_start    = August 5, 1886\n| term_end      = August 9, 1891\n| appointer     = [[operation of law]]\n| predecessor   = ''Seat established by 24 Stat. 308''\n| successor     = [[William W. Morrow]]\n| office1       = Judge of the [[United States District Court for the District of California]]\n| term_start1   = July 27, 1866\n| term_end1     = August 5, 1886\n| appointer1    = [[operation of law]]\n| predecessor1  = ''Seat established by 14 Stat. 300''\n| successor1    = ''Seat abolished''\n| office2       = Judge of the [[United States District Court for the Southern District of California]]\n| term_start2   = August 31, 1852\n| term_end2     = January 18, 1854\n| appointer2    = [[operation of law]]\n| predecessor2  = ''Seat established by 10 Stat. 76''\n| successor2    = ''Seat abolished''\n| office3       = Judge of the [[United States District Court for the Northern District of California]]\n| term_start3   = February 27, 1851\n| term_end3     = July 27, 1866\n| appointer3    = [[List of federal judges appointed by Millard Fillmore|Millard Fillmore]]\n| predecessor3  = ''Seat established by 9 Stat. 521''\n| successor3    = ''Seat abolished''\n| birth_name    = Ogden Hoffman Jr.\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date|1822|10|16}}\n| birth_place   = [[New York City]], [[New York (state)|New York]]\n| death_date    = {{Death date and age|1891|08|09|1822|10|16}}\n| death_place   = [[San Francisco]], [[California]]\n| resting_place = [[Mount Tamalpais Cemetery]]<br>[[San Rafael, California|San Rafael]], [[California]]\n| party         =\n| otherparty    =\n| spouse        =\n| children      =\n| parents       = [[Ogden Hoffman]]<br/>Emily (Burrall) Hoffman\n| relatives     = [[Josiah Ogden Hoffman]] (grandfather)\n| education     = [[Columbia University]] {{midsize|([[Bachelor of Arts|A.B.]])}}<br>[[Harvard Law School]] {{midsize|([[Bachelor of Laws|LL.B.]])}}\n| occupation    = Attorney\n}}\n\n'''Ogden Hoffman Jr.''' (October 16, 1822 \u2013 August 9, 1891) was a [[United States federal judge|United States District Judge]] of the [[United States District Court for the District of California]], the [[United States District Court for the Northern District of California]] and the [[United States District Court for the Southern District of California]].\n\n==Education and career==\nBorn on October 16, 1822, in [[New York City]], [[New York (state)|New York]], Hoffman received an [[Bachelor of Arts|Artium Baccalaureus]] degree in 1840 from [[Columbia University]] and a [[Bachelor of Laws]] in 1842 from [[Harvard Law School]]. He entered private practice in New York City in 1842, and from 1844 to 1850. He continued private practice in [[San Francisco]], [[California]] from 1850 to 1851.<ref name=\"auto\">{{FJC Bio|1065|nid=1382256|name=Ogden Hoffman Jr.<!--(1822\u20131891)-->}}</ref>\n\n==Federal judicial service==\nHoffman was nominated by President [[Millard Fillmore]] on February 1, 1851, to the [[United States District Court for the Northern District of California]], to a new seat authorized by 9 Stat. 521. He was confirmed by the [[United States Senate]] on February 27, 1851, and received his commission the same day. Hoffman was assigned by [[operation of law]] to additional and concurrent service on the [[United States District Court for the Southern District of California]] on August 31, 1852, to a new seat authorized by 10 Stat. 76. His service in the Southern District terminated on January 18, 1854. Hoffman was reassigned by [[operation of law]] to the [[United States District Court for the District of California]] on July 27, 1866, to a new seat authorized by 14 Stat. 300. Hoffman was reassigned by [[operation of law]] to the [[United States District Court for the Northern District of California]] on August 5, 1886, to a new seat authorized by 24 Stat. 308. His service terminated on August 9, 1891, due to his death in San Francisco. He was succeeded by Judge [[William W. Morrow]].<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\n==Death and burial==\nHoffman died in San Francisco on August 9, 1891. He was interred at [[Mount Tamalpais Cemetery]] in [[San Rafael, California|San Rafael]], California.<ref>{{Find a Grave|91513914}}</ref>\n\n==Family==\nHoffman was son of [[Ogden Hoffman]] (1794\u20131856) and Emily (Burrall) Hoffman. He was the grandson of [[Josiah Ogden Hoffman]] (1766\u20131837), the [[New York Attorney General]] from 1795 to 1802.{{Citation needed|date=May 2019}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Sources==\n* {{FJC Bio|1065|nid=1382256|name=Ogden Hoffman Jr.<!--(1822\u20131891)-->}}\n* {{Find a Grave|91513914}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-legal}}\n{{s-bef|before=Seat established by 9 Stat. 521}}\n{{s-ttl|title={{nowrap|Judge of the [[United States District Court for the Northern District of California]]}}|years=1851\u20131866}}\n{{s-aft|after=Seat abolished}}\n{{s-bef|before=Seat established by 10 Stat. 76}}\n{{s-ttl|title={{nowrap|Judge of the [[United States District Court for the Southern District of California]]}}|years=1852\u20131854}}\n{{s-aft|after=Seat abolished}}\n{{s-bef|before=Seat established by 14 Stat. 300}}\n{{s-ttl|title={{nowrap|Judge of the [[United States District Court for the District of California]]}}|years=1866\u20131886}}\n{{s-aft|after=Seat abolished}}\n{{s-bef|before=Seat established by 24 Stat. 308}}\n{{s-ttl|title={{nowrap|Judge of the [[United States District Court for the Northern District of California]]}}|years=1886\u20131891}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[William W. Morrow]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hoffman, Ogden Jr.}}\n[[Category:1822 births]]\n[[Category:1891 deaths]]\n[[Category:Columbia College (New York) alumni]]\n[[Category:Judges of the United States District Court for the Northern District of California]]\n[[Category:Judges of the United States District Court for the Southern District of California]]\n[[Category:Judges of the United States District Court for the District of California]]\n[[Category:United States federal judges appointed by Millard Fillmore]]\n[[Category:19th-century American judges]]\n[[Category:Hoffman family|Ogden Jr.]]\n[[Category:Harvard Law School alumni]]\n[[Category:19th-century American politicians]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|American judge}}\n{{Infobox judge\n| name          = Ogden Hoffman Jr.\n| image         = Ogden Hoffman, Jr. (Federal judge of California).jpg\n| caption       = Judge Ogden Hoffman Jr. ''San Francisco Call'', December 19, 1893.\n| office        = Judge of the [[United States District Court for the Northern District of California]]\n| term_start    = August 5, 1886\n| term_end      = August 9, 1891\n| appointer     = [[operation of law]]\n| predecessor   = ''Seat established by 24 Stat. 308''\n| successor     = [[William W. Morrow]]\n| office1       = Judge of the [[United States District Court for the District of California]]\n| term_start1   = July 27, 1866\n| term_end1     = August 5, 1886\n| appointer1    = [[operation of law]]\n| predecessor1  = ''Seat established by 14 Stat. 300''\n| successor1    = ''Seat abolished''\n| office2       = Judge of the [[United States District Court for the Southern District of California]]\n| term_start2   = August 31, 1852\n| term_end2     = January 18, 1854\n| appointer2    = [[operation of law]]\n| predecessor2  = ''Seat established by 10 Stat. 76''\n| successor2    = ''Seat abolished''\n| office3       = Judge of the [[United States District Court for the Northern District of California]]\n| term_start3   = February 27, 1851\n| term_end3     = July 27, 1866\n| appointer3    = [[List of federal judges appointed by Millard Fillmore|Millard Fillmore]]\n| predecessor3  = ''Seat established by 9 Stat. 521''\n| successor3    = ''Seat abolished''\n| birth_name    = Ogden Hoffman Jr.\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date|1822|10|16}}\n| birth_place   = [[New York City]], [[New York (state)|New York]]\n| death_date    = {{Death date and age|1891|08|09|1822|10|16}}\n| death_place   = [[San Francisco]], [[California]]\n| resting_place = [[Mount Tamalpais Cemetery]]<br>[[San Rafael, California|San Rafael]], [[California]]\n| party         =\n| otherparty    =\n| spouse        =\n| children      =\n| parents       = [[Ogden Hoffman]]\n| relatives     = [[Josiah Ogden Hoffman]] (grandfather)\n| education     = [[Columbia University]] {{midsize|([[Bachelor of Arts|A.B.]])}}<br>[[Harvard Law School]] {{midsize|([[Bachelor of Laws|LL.B.]])}}\n| occupation    = Attorney\n}}\n\n'''Ogden Hoffman Jr.''' (October 16, 1822 \u2013 August 9, 1891) was a [[United States federal judge|United States District Judge]] of the [[United States District Court for the District of California]], the [[United States District Court for the Northern District of California]] and the [[United States District Court for the Southern District of California]].\n\n==Education and career==\nBorn on October 16, 1822, in [[New York City]], [[New York (state)|New York]], Hoffman received an [[Bachelor of Arts|Artium Baccalaureus]] degree in 1840 from [[Columbia University]] and a [[Bachelor of Laws]] in 1842 from [[Harvard Law School]]. He entered private practice in New York City in 1842, and from 1844 to 1850. He continued private practice in [[San Francisco]], [[California]] from 1850 to 1851.<ref name=\"auto\">{{FJC Bio|1065|nid=1382256|name=Ogden Hoffman Jr.<!--(1822\u20131891)-->}}</ref>\n\n==Federal judicial service==\nHoffman was nominated by President [[Millard Fillmore]] on February 1, 1851, to the [[United States District Court for the Northern District of California]], to a new seat authorized by 9 Stat. 521. He was confirmed by the [[United States Senate]] on February 27, 1851, and received his commission the same day. Hoffman was assigned by [[operation of law]] to additional and concurrent service on the [[United States District Court for the Southern District of California]] on August 31, 1852, to a new seat authorized by 10 Stat. 76. His service in the Southern District terminated on January 18, 1854. Hoffman was reassigned by [[operation of law]] to the [[United States District Court for the District of California]] on July 27, 1866, to a new seat authorized by 14 Stat. 300. Hoffman was reassigned by [[operation of law]] to the [[United States District Court for the Northern District of California]] on August 5, 1886, to a new seat authorized by 24 Stat. 308. His service terminated on August 9, 1891, due to his death in San Francisco. He was succeeded by Judge [[William W. Morrow]].<ref name=\"auto\"/> He was interred in [[Mount Tamalpais Cemetery]] in [[San Rafael, California|San Rafael]], California.<ref>{{Find a Grave|91513914}}</ref>\n\n==Family==\nHoffman was son of [[Ogden Hoffman]] (1794\u20131856) and Emily Burrall, and the grandson of [[Josiah Ogden Hoffman]] (1766\u20131837), the [[New York Attorney General]] from 1795 to 1802.{{Citation needed|date=May 2019}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Sources==\n* {{FJC Bio|1065|nid=1382256|name=Ogden Hoffman Jr.<!--(1822\u20131891)-->}}\n* {{Find a Grave|91513914}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-legal}}\n{{s-bef|before=Seat established by 9 Stat. 521}}\n{{s-ttl|title={{nowrap|Judge of the [[United States District Court for the Northern District of California]]}}|years=1851\u20131866}}\n{{s-aft|after=Seat abolished}}\n{{s-bef|before=Seat established by 10 Stat. 76}}\n{{s-ttl|title={{nowrap|Judge of the [[United States District Court for the Southern District of California]]}}|years=1852\u20131854}}\n{{s-aft|after=Seat abolished}}\n{{s-bef|before=Seat established by 14 Stat. 300}}\n{{s-ttl|title={{nowrap|Judge of the [[Unite